The paper focuses on image understanding tasks, specifically group-level emotion recognition and event recognition, which are highly semantic and require the interaction of several deep models to synthesize multiple cues. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of graph neural networks (GNNs) indicates that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The mention of a new group-level emotion recognition database suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple cues and the need for information exchange among features suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
